      <Content>Despite certain differences in size, in some languages the closest natural equivalent of the phrase βῆμα ποδός is simply ‘a square foot,’ while in other languages employing the metric system, a phrase such as ‘a square meter’ would be more appropriate. Some languages, however, may employ expressions such as ‘the measure of an arm’s length’ or ‘the ground of one stride.’ The focal point in {S:04400700500018} is not so much the specific measurement, but rather the very limited space.</Content>
