          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-05 11:07:55" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>a raised platform mounted by steps and usually furnished with a seat; used by officials to address an assembly, often on judicial matters, with a focus on judgement</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>judgement seat</Gloss>
                <Gloss>judgment place</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The association of a βῆμα with judicial procedures means that there is almost always an important component of judicial function associated with this term. Therefore in translating βῆμα, it is often best to use a phrase such as ‘a place where a judge decides’ or ‘a place where decisions are made’ or ‘a judge’s seat.’ The focus upon judgment is particularly important in those passages which refer to the judgment seat of God ({S:04501401000040}) and of Christ ({S:04700501000018}).</Comments>
